reviews.headline: I have bought this again and again.
reviews.comments: I have been using IT for years and years.  I have tried other foundations from time to time but have always went back to IT.

reviews.headline: Please don't EVER discontinue this! Great for mature skin!
reviews.comments: As a woman of 50 with extremely dry skin with a lot of redness and freckles, finding a luminous full coverage foundation that does NOT dry out my skin and does NOT exaggerate my fine lines has been next to impossible. I tried all the brands... Nars, Dior, Lancome, Hourglass, you name it... they all had issues. Either they were drying, they did not match my skin or were too sheer to cover up my redness. I had been using IT full coverage foundations for years, but as I aged, I found it drying to my skin. Enter this IT Full Coverage Moisturizer with SPF. Finally! It works! It's a bit more sheer than I'm used to, but is buildable without being too much. It lasts all day, and does not dry my skin out. I'm so, so happy to have found it. Please don't ever stop making it!!

reviews.headline: Not what it used to be
reviews.comments: Has the formula changed?  Doesn't cover like it used to cover.  Used to use 1 pump now have to use 2 pumps of IT Bye Bye Foundation Full Coverage Moisturizer with SPF 50+.  Too expensive, price went up by $10.00.

reviews.headline: Best coverage!
reviews.comments: perfect amount of coverage and just the right tone!

reviews.headline: BEST. FOUNDATION. EVER.
reviews.comments: PERFECT FOUNDATION FOR MATURE SKIN. COVERAGE IS GREAT, BUT FOUNDATION IS ALSO LIGHTWEIGHT. THE MOISTURE ELEMENT MAKES IT GO ON SMOOTHLY AND EASILY AND MY SKIN GLOWS FOR HOURS. FULL SUNSCREEN WHICH SAVES ME FROM HAVING TO APPLY THIS UNDER MY MAKEUP. THE ONLY PROBLEM IS THAT MY STORE DECIDED TO STOP CARRYING THIS PARTICULAR FOUNDATION (THE ONE WITH MOISTURE). WHY, OH WHY???

reviews.headline: Amazing
reviews.comments: Im so happy i went online and matched my skin tone and it matched my skin tones light and i will definitely buy more often i will definitely will wear in spring and winter

reviews.headline: I buy this product when Ultra has in stock
reviews.comments: This foundation is great.  Ulta is often out when I go to replace.

reviews.headline: The Holy Grail of Foundations
reviews.comments: This is the ultimate holy grail of foundations. It is thick, smooth, weightless, luxuriously soft, and covers like a magic marker. You can't even tell I have it on, but it makes my skin look flawless. My only complaint is that I run out so fast!

reviews.headline: Great product
reviews.comments: I am in my 30s with dry skin and some fine lines. I have repurchased this at least 3 times and always come back to it for my day to day. It is thick and moisturizing but also covers well. I apply with fingers and  I love the dewy finish. It just works and I know when I slap it on in the morning that I will have a good skin day. I like this way better than their cc cream because I find the finish more natural and it absorbs into my skin rather than sitting on it.

reviews.headline: I'm now buying second bottle!
reviews.comments: I really love this foundation. It can cause texture but as long as you use a silicone based primer you're good to go! it lasts all day, doesn't dry my skin, and doesn't cause acne for me!

reviews.headline: Sad wasn't a fan
reviews.comments: Bought this because it says moisturizing foundation, and im always looking for something full coverage due to rosacea, it  was not moisturizing and it did not cover my rocesea, was very disappointed and it was thick i did not like the way it felt on my skin at all.

reviews.headline: My favorite makeup!
reviews.comments: The perfect flawless coverage for my skin. I have tried higher end brands of makeup and always return to IT ByeBye full coverage.

reviews.headline: Love it!
reviews.comments: I have acne prone skin and it works perfect on me!

reviews.headline: I love this product!!
reviews.comments: Every now and then I'll try a new foundation, just for kicks. Every time, I come right back to this one. The coverage is unmatched! It doesn't cake or flake, good for all day wear (14+ hours!).

reviews.headline: Multiple Time Buyer
reviews.comments: This is and has been my go to foundation for years. Perfect for every occasion and belnds into skin really well. Perfect amount of coverage to blur without covering natural color

reviews.headline: Foundation
reviews.comments: My favorite foundation. It has spf, long lasting and smells good too. A little goes a long way

reviews.headline: This is the only makeup I will buy .
reviews.comments: This makeup is weightless and makes my skin appear bright and healthy.

reviews.headline: I have been using this for years
reviews.comments: I really like this foundation. It goes on nicely and looks beautiful!

reviews.headline: This is the best foundation I have ever used! It has it all.
reviews.comments: It has everything I want in a foundation... it's a moisturizer, it's full coverage and it has SPF 50!! I have tried several different matte foundations but hated them because it drying and shows too much texture but the ByeBye Foundation/moisturizer is hydrating and smooth on my 44 year old skin.

media.headline: Love it!  I have been using for about a year.  All pros - no
LOVE LOVE LOVE I now prefer this over IT CC Cream

faceoff_positive.comments: I'm a daily wearer of IT Cosmetics CC cream and I can easily see distinct differences between the two.  I'm 39 YO with Oily skin and visible pores and always fighting those fine lines.  I'm exactly between their CC Fair and Light shades, so I have to blend the two colors together daily.  I saw  this release of the Fair/Light color so I was excited to try it. The Fair/Light shade has a definite PINK undertone, but it's definitely still workable for me.  I wore it today with no moisturizer and no primer (I always wear both) and it's holding up much better than the CC cream!  For me the product provided better coverage than the CC cream while using less of it.  It also dried down to a natural finish pretty quickly.  CC always leaves me with a tacky, luminous, almost wet looking finish before I powder it in order to apply the rest of my make, but I didn't have to even powder with this!  I'm extremely happy with how it looks on my skin, and amazed that I didn't have to use as many products either.  I highly recommend!
faceoff_positive.headline: LOVE LOVE LOVE I now prefer this over IT CC Cream

faceoff_negative.comments: The IT cosmetics CC cream was my foundation of choice for months, but recently I was on the lookout for something different and thought this would be a perfect alternative. Boy was I wrong. I've never had an adverse reaction to makeup before nor do I have sensitive skin so I was shocked to discover that this product broke me out horribly. My skin is now red, irritated, dry, itchy, and covered in both small bumps and cystic acne as a result of this foundation. I'm embarrassed to leave my dorm since my skin is constantly inflamed and in pain, and I can hardly stand to look at myself in the mirror. I'm horrified and appalled that this company would release a product like this, claiming it can help skin conditions such as acne, dryness, and redness when it actually exacerbates all of those issues. To say the least, I would suggest that you stay as far away from this foundation as possible.
faceoff_negative.headline: Worst Breakout of My Life
